title: Garlic And Herb Sweet Potato Fries
directions: Line a baking tray with parchment paper and set aside.
Slice the sweet potatoes, with skin on, into 1/4 inch by 1/4 inch batons (fries).
Place the sweet potatoes on the baking sheet and toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper until evenly coated.
Place in the oven for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown and starting to burn on the edges. Toss the fries once after 10 minutes.
Remove the fries from the oven and top with cheese/garlic/parsley mixture.
